, and has been since 1854.','California State','','publish','open','open','','california-state','','','2015-02-02 03:32:43','2015-02-02 03:32:43','',1957,'http://shinetheme.com/demosd/traveler_demo/?post_type=location&amp;p=1944',0,'location','',0),(1945,2,'2015-02-02 03:39:40','2015-02-02 03:39:40','Los Angeles, officially the City of Los Angeles, often known by its initials L.A., is a major city in California\'s Southern California region, approximately 342 miles (551 km) south of San Francisco. With a population of 3,792,621 as of 2010, Los Angeles is the second-largest city in the United States, after New York City, and the most populous city in California. Los Angeles is known for its mediterranean climate, ethnic diversity, celebrity culture, traffic, and the film and television industry.','Los Angeles','','publish','open','open','','los-angeles','','','2015-02-02 03:39:40','2015-02-02 03:39:40','',1944,'http://shinetheme.com/demosd/traveler_demo/?post_type=location&amp;p=1945',0,'location','',0),(1946,2,'2015-02-02 03:45:43','2015-02-02 03:45:43','San Francisco, officially the City and County of San Francisco, is the cultural, commercial and financial center of Northern California.\n\nThe only consolidated city-county in California,[24] San Francisco encompasses a land area of about 46.9 square miles (121 km2)[25] on the northern end of the San Francisco Peninsula, giving it a density of about 17,867 people per square mile (6,898 people per km2). It is the most densely settled large city (population greater than 200,000) in the state of California and the second-most densely populated major city in the United States after New York City.[26] San Francisco is the fourth-most populous city in California, after Los Angeles, San Diego and San Jose, and the 14th-most populous city in the United States—with a Census-estimated 2013 population of 837,442.[21] The city and its surroundings are known as the San Francisco Bay Area, part of the San Jose-San Francisco-Oakland combined statistical area, with an estimated population of 8.5 million.','San Francisco','','publish','open','open','','san-francisco','','','2015-02-02 03:45:43','2015-02-02 03:45:43','',1944,'http://shinetheme.com/demosd/traveler_demo/?post_type=location&amp;p=1946',0,'location','',0),(1947,2,'2015-02-02 03:56:49','2015-02-02 03:56:49','Nevada is a state in the Western, Mountain West, and Southwestern regions of the United States. Nevada is the 7th most extensive, the 35th most populous, and the 9th least densely populated of the 50 United States. Nearly three-quarters of Nevada\'s people live in Clark County, which contains the Las Vegas–Paradise metropolitan area where the state\'s three largest incorporated cities are located. Nevada\'s capital is Carson City. Nevada is officially known as the \"Silver State\" due to the importance of silver to its history and economy. It is also known as the \"Battle Born State\", because it achieved statehood during the Civil War; as the \"Sagebrush State\", for the native plant of the same name; and as \"Sage hen State\".','Nevada State','','publish','open','open','','nevada','','','2015-02-02 03:56:49','2015-02-02 03:56:49','',1957,'http://shinetheme.com/demosd/traveler_demo/?post_type=location&amp;p=1947',0,'location','',0),(1952,2,'2015-02-02 04:06:27','2015-02-02 04:06:27','Virginia, officially the Commonwealth of Virginia, is a U.S. state located in the South Atlantic region of the United States. Virginia is nicknamed the \"Old Dominion\" due to its status as a former dominion of the English Crown, and \"Mother of Presidents\" due to the most U.S. presidents having been born there. The geography and climate of the Commonwealth are shaped by the Blue Ridge Mountains and the Chesapeake Bay, which provide habitat for much of its flora and fauna. The capital of the Commonwealth is Richmond; Virginia Beach is the most populous city, and Fairfax County is the most populous political subdivision. The Commonwealth\'s estimated population as of 2014 is over 8.3 million.','Virginia  State','','publish','open','open','','virginia-state','','','2015-02-02 04:06:27','2015-02-02 04:06:27','',1957,'http://shinetheme.com/demosd/traveler_demo/?post_type=location&amp;p=1952',0,'location','',0),(1957,2,'2015-02-02 04:22:16','2015-02-02 04:22:16','[vc_row parallax_class=\"yes\" el_class=\"location_row_fix\" css=\".vc_custom_1434103488948{background-image: url(http://shinetheme.com/demosd/traveler/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/wood.jpg?id=5077) !important;}\"][vc_column css=\".vc_custom_1434335122854{padding-top: 60px !important;padding-bottom: 100px !important;}\"][vc_column_text]\n<h1 style=\"color: white; text-align: center;\">Welcome to United States</h1>\n[/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner css=\".vc_custom_1434336408035{background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.01) !important;*background-color: rgb(255,255,255) !important;}\" el_class=\"location_header\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\" css=\".vc_custom_1434336351502{background-color: rgba(221,221,221,0.01) !important;*background-color: rgb(221,221,221) !important;}\"][st_location_header_rate_count st_location_header_rate_count_post_type=\"st_hotel,st_cars,st_rental,st_activity,st_tours\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\" css=\".vc_custom_1434336342845{background-color: rgba(219,219,219,0.01) !important;*background-color: rgb(219,219,219) !important;}\"][st_location_header_static st_location_header_rate_count_to=\"st_hotel,st_cars,st_rental,st_activity,st_tours\" st_location_star_list=\"5,4,3,2,1\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1434336702540{margin-top: -50px !important;}\"][vc_column][vc_tabs interval=\"0\" tab_style=\"search_tab\" el_class=\"location_tab_nopadding\"][vc_tab tab_icon=\"fa fa-info\" title=\"Information\" tab_id=\"01e3fb61-8a32-3\"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][st_location_slider st_location_list_image=\"5325,5324,5323,5322,5321,5320\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_colu